Finally, the codification of access captures how access is legally regulated, and thus its revocability by distinguishing between regulation through treaties, secondary legislation, or bureaucratic decisions (scores ranging between through treaty provision, to secondary legislation and bureaucratic decisions).

Composite index: Access = 1/n * [sum of all] (range + depth) * Permanence * Codification

Where the permanence and codification variables are multiplied against range and depth as weights on the access. I.e. high scores in range and depth have relatively lower scores where participation is ad hoc and granted by non-binding sources (because it is unstable).

